Codec Constructor Notes zstd <code>zarr.codecs.ZstdCodec(level, checksum)</code> levels −131072…22, default 0; zarr-python's default compressor blosc <code>zarr.codecs.BloscCodec(cname=…, clevel=…, shuffle=…)</code> cname: <code>lz4</code>, <code>lz4hc</code>, <code>blosclz</code>, <code>zstd</code>, <code>zlib</code>; shuffle: <code>noshuffle</code>/<code>shuffle</code>/<code>bitshuffle</code>; typesize auto-filled from the dtype gzip <code>zarr.codecs.GzipCodec(level)</code> levels 0–9, default 5; pure Java, no MEX needed crc32c <code>zarr.codecs.Crc32cCodec()</code> 4-byte checksum, verified on read transpose <code>zarr.codecs.TransposeCodec(order)</code> 0-based dimension permutation bytes <code>zarr.codecs.BytesCodec(endian)</code> serializer; <code>"little"</code> (default) or <code>"big"</code> <pre><code>zb = zarr.create(store, [64 64], "single", ChunkShape=[32 32], Path="b", ...
    Codecs={zarr.codecs.BloscCodec(cname="lz4", clevel=9, shuffle="shuffle")});
p = single(peaks(64));
zb(:, :) = p;
assert(isequal(zb(:, :), p))
</code></pre>
